      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. GCI on the relative hemolysis index is 3.2% on the fine mesh (7.4 M cells), satisfying the 5% threshold. Medium mesh (3.1 M cells) used for parametric sweep as cost-accuracy compromise."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) must match CFD inlet/outlet conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "Laboratory test conditions documented in the experimental reference dataset span flow rates 2–6 L/min and rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM. CFD boundary conditions replicate these within 2.1% for flow rate and 0.8% for rotational speed. Fluid viscosity matched to blood analog (water-glycerol 40%) within ±1.5%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index must agree with experimental measurements within 15% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements at 5 operating points. Maximum deviation is 11.3% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM condition; all other points within 8%. Mean absolute error across operating points is 6.7%, satisfying the 15% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs computed by the model (NIH, RH index) must directly map to the clinical acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed directly from CFD-predicted shear stress history integrated along particle pathlines using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. RH maps one-to-one to the regulatory acceptance criterion. NIH provides secondary corroboration against ISO 10993-4 reference limits."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
