      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published precedent for rotating blood-contacting devices. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Literature survey of five comparable CFD hemolysis studies confirms k-ω SST as standard practice for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary condition inputs must be traceable to measured or published data; sensitivity to key inputs documented.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions sourced from the pump-geometry-boundary-conditions dataset (vintage 2025-10-31). Inlet flow rates, outlet pressure, and rotational speed are traceable to bench measurements. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for inlet flow rate (±10%) and rotational speed (±5%), confirming RH index changes within ±8%. Re-validation against the updated model revision (2026-02-14) is planned for Q2 2026 but has not yet been completed; current inputs reflect the prior model build."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
